{"title": "Weaponized Camera", "content": "So there's a fight scene, and someone just happens to have a camera. Not only is the camera useful for snapping photographs, it's one more possible weapon out of many already present in the scene. If the camera isn't being used to physically bonk people over the head, the flash can be used to momentarily blind them . In some rare cases, the effectiveness of the camera as a weapon has to do with superstition on the part of the person whose picture gets taken (\"You stole my soul!\"). An Art Attacker may have one of these as their weapon.\n\nWhen the camera's offensive properties go beyond just the flash or a simple bludgeon, it's likely a Magical Camera.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponizedCamera", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SpeedGrapher", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/ZombiePowder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Batman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Cavewoman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ToyStory2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DeathTrain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DogSoldiers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DontBeAfraidOfTheDark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DrNo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Gremlins", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HalloweenResurrection", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/HellraiserIIIHellOnEarth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Inside", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/MurderAtTheBaskervilles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ParanormalActivity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePoughkeepsieTapes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Quarantine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/RearWindow", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheSleeper", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/YoureNext", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Goosebumps", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/MichaelCrichton", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Prey", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLaundryFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KolchakTheNightStalker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/HogansHeroes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Se